{ Here the winning chances are great, too. The only situation worth studying occurs when the enemy king threatens the pawns. However, usually the pawns have one of these resources at their disposal:

1) Mutual defence: one pawn threatens to promote to avoid the capture of the other one.
2) Delay the capture of one pawn until the strong king arrives to defend them and reaches the key squares of the other one. }
